      • getWaypointID

        public int getWaypointID()
        Get the waypoint identifier for this waypoint.

        The Waypoint ID is a unique integer identifier for the Waypoint; the value is positive and with each new waypoint the value increments by one.

        Returns:
        the waypoint identifier.

      • getProsecutionOrder

        public short getProsecutionOrder()
        Get the prosecution order.

        The Prosecution Order value is the position in the order of operation list. Planned waypoints are positive (i.e., >0) values. The current waypoint has a value of zero. Historical waypoints have negative values (i.e., <0) in decreasing order. (i.e., each completed waypoint has its Prosecution Order set to the next largest magnitude negative number). To determine the last waypoint, take the min value of all Prosecution Orders. Historical waypoints become static records, requiring updates only once every 30 seconds if retained. When canceling a waypoint set its Prosecution Order to the maximum positive value to indicate cancellation; this is the only value where multiple Waypoint Records can use the same Prosecution Order.

        Returns:
        the prosecution order

      • setProsecutionOrder

        Set the prosecution order.

        The Prosecution Order value is the position in the order of operation list. Planned waypoints are positive (i.e., >0) values. The current waypoint has a value of zero. Historical waypoints have negative values (i.e., <0) in decreasing order. (i.e., each completed waypoint has its Prosecution Order set to the next largest magnitude negative number). To determine the last waypoint, take the min value of all Prosecution Orders. Historical waypoints become static records, requiring updates only once every 30 seconds if retained. When canceling a waypoint set its Prosecution Order to the maximum positive value to indicate cancellation; this is the only value where multiple Waypoint Records can use the same Prosecution Order.

        Parameters:
